  "text": "While several heuristics like Degree Discount [CITATION_1] and IRIE [CITATION_2] were developed to efficiently find IM solutions, their accuracy were not theoretical guaranteed. Improved approximation algorithms include CELF [CITATION_3] and CELF++ [CITATION_4] . Recently, Borgs [CITATION_5] showed his reverse influence sampling runtime-optimal with accuracy guarantees.",
